{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Mat|28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","chapter":28,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":1,"text":"After the Sabbath, as the first day of the week was dawning, Mary Magdalene and the other Mary went to view the tomb.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":2,"text":"There was a violent earthquake, because an angel of the Lord descended from heaven and approached the tomb. He rolled back the stone and was sitting on it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":3,"text":"His appearance was like lightning, and his clothing was as white as snow.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":4,"text":"The guards were so shaken by fear of him that they became like dead men.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":5,"text":"The angel told the women, “Don’t be afraid, because I know you are looking for Jesus who was crucified.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":6,"text":"He is not here. For he has risen, just as he said. Come and see the place where he lay.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":7,"text":"Then go quickly and tell his disciples, ‘He has risen from the dead and indeed he is going ahead of you to Galilee; you will see him there.’ Listen, I have told you.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":8,"text":"So, departing quickly from the tomb with fear and great joy, they ran to tell his disciples the news.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":9,"text":"Just then Jesus met them and said, “Greetings!” They came up, took hold of his feet, and worshiped him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":10,"text":"Then Jesus told them, “Do not be afraid. Go and tell my brothers to leave for Galilee, and they will see me there.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":11,"text":"As they were on their way, some of the guards came into the city and reported to the chief priests everything that had happened.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":12,"text":"After the priests had assembled with the elders and agreed on a plan, they gave the soldiers a large sum of money","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":13,"text":"and told them, “Say this, ‘His disciples came during the night and stole him while we were sleeping.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":14,"text":"If this reaches the governor’s ears, we will deal with him and keep you out of trouble.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":15,"text":"They took the money and did as they were instructed, and this story has been spread among Jewish people to this day.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":16,"text":"The eleven disciples traveled to Galilee, to the mountain where Jesus had directed them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":17,"text":"When they saw him, they worshiped, but some doubted.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":18,"text":"Jesus came near and said to them, “All authority has been given to me in heaven and on earth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":19,"text":"Go, therefore, and make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:28:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":28,"verse":20,"text":"teaching them to observe everything I have commanded you. And remember, I am with you always, to the end of the age.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","chapter":28,"paragraphStarts":[1,5,8,11,16],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Resurrection Morning"},{"beforeV